   =20
<div class=3D"content-block-regular"><p>The 1970s were a transformative dec=
ade for muscle cars, marking both the peak of raw power and the beginning o=
f a     <span class=3D"display-card-hyperlink-article" data-id=3D"19406"><a=
 href=3D"https://www.hotcars.com/best-muscle-car-malaise-era/" target=3D"_b=
lank">shift toward more regulated performance</a></span>. The 1960s set the=
 scene for the     <span class=3D"display-card-hyperlink-article" data-id=
=3D"1033743"><a href=3D"https://www.hotcars.com/american-classic-car-icons/=
" target=3D"_blank">golden era of American muscle car performance</a></span=
>, and many manufacturers raced to develop a car that could excite the publ=
ic and capitalize on the press of the ongoing horsepower wars. Sky-high oup=
uts and     <span class=3D"display-card-hyperlink-article" data-id=3D"10408=
57"><a href=3D"https://www.hotcars.com/fastest-60s-muscle-cars-quarter-mile=
/" target=3D"_blank">quick quarter mile times</a></span> served as the ulti=
mate benchmark for muscle car prowess.    </p>    <!-- No AdsNinja v10 Clie=
nt! --><!-- No AdsNinja v10 Client! --><p>Of course, we know now that these=
 days of plenty didn't last for long. By the mid-1970s, the onset of tighte=
ning emissions regulations had strangled many muscle cars, and their     <s=
pan class=3D"display-card-hyperlink-article" data-id=3D"1004613"><a href=3D=
"https://www.hotcars.com/here-is-why-malaise-cars-will-never-be-worth-anyth=
ing/" target=3D"_blank">performance numbers were reduced</a></span> to hazy=
 impressions of their former glory. However, there are some quick cars to b=
e had in those first few years of the decade, and we've done our due dilige=
nce to compile only the quickest of the lot. Having scoured the net for the=
 most     <span class=3D"display-card-hyperlink-article" data-id=3D"28400">=
<a href=3D"https://www.hotcars.com/coolest-american-cars-of-the-1970s/" tar=
get=3D"_blank">impressive 1970s muscle cars</a></span>, here are 10 of the =
fastest we've found through the quarter mile.    </p>           =20
